        "body": "## Summary\n\n- convert case-insensitive `<br>`, `<br/>`, and `<br />` forms inside Markdown table cells to newline characters\n- preserve existing bold, italic, code, and link handling in table cells\n- leave non-table Markdown parsing unchanged\n- add parser and Google Docs insertion-request regression tests\n\nThanks @sebsnyk for the report and concrete reproduction in https://github.com/openclaw/gogcli/issues/730.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `go test ./internal/cmd -run 'TestParseMarkdown.*Table|TestDocsWrite.*Markdown|Test.*Table.*Inline'`\n- `make fmt`\n- `make test`\n- Redacted live Google Docs proof: confirm `Alice<br>Bob<br>Carol` renders as three lines in one cell when authenticated validation is available; otherwise note the environment limitation and attach the insertion-request proof.\n\nMarkdown hard breaks using two trailing spaces are intentionally not added unless they can be represented unambiguously by the existing single-line pipe-table grammar.\n\nCloses https://github.com/openclaw/gogcli/issues/730\n\nClawSweeper 🐠 replacement reef notes:\n- Cluster: issue-openclaw-gogcli-730\n- Source PRs: none\n- Credit: Credit @sebsnyk for reporting the table-cell line-break defect and providing the concrete CLI reproduction in https://github.com/openclaw/gogcli/issues/730.; Preserve user-visible release-note context in the PR body; do not edit CHANGELOG.md in this automated repair lane.; Include redacted live Google Docs proof in the PR validation notes when executor credentials permit it; otherwise clearly record that automated parser and request-generation tests provide the reproducible proof.\n- Validation: go test ./internal/cmd -run 'TestParseMarkdown.*Table|TestDocsWrite.*Markdown|Test.*Table.*Inline'; make fmt; make test\n- Replacement reason: ClawSweeper could not update the source PR branch directly, so it opened a writable replacement PR instead.\n\n<!-- clawsweeper-source-issue repo=openclaw/gogcli number=730 snapshot=222741cea9c24b185